d on the linked site in the section \"Measurement\". There you will also find a tally sheet and links to instructions on how to analyse the data found in the dataset. The section \"Identifying Pariticles\" will show how to find out which detector signature hints at which particle. \"Identifying Events\" details how to categorise events. Using the knowledge of these two sections, one can use the prescriptions in \"Measurement\" to find out how the proton is structured and to hunt for the Higgs particle.","links":[{"url":"http://atlas.physicsmasterclasses.org/en/wpath_ziele.htm"}]}},"updated":"2025-06-06T07:25:05.185797+00:00"}],"total":159},"links":{"next":"https://opendata.cern.ch/api/records/?experiment=ATLAS&type=Dataset&sort=mostrecent&size=1&page=2","self":"https://opendata.cern.ch/api/records/?experiment=ATLAS&type=Dataset&sort=mostrecent&size=1&page=1"}}